---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Seat-Based Pricing | ${siteName}`}
  description="Seat-based pricing definition, when it works, and when to add usage tiers or minimums."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Seat-based pricing</h1>
    <p>Seat-based pricing charges based on the number of users. Itâ€™s simple to buy, but it can break when costs scale with usage.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>When seats work well</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Value scales with number of users (collaboration, workflow tools).</li>
        <li>Usage per user is fairly predictable.</li>
        <li>Budgets are naturally per headcount.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">When to add a usage component</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Automation drives high consumption with few seats.</li>
        <li>Infra or vendor costs spike for power users.</li>
        <li>Customers can extract large value without adding users.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/seat-vs-usage-pricing-comparison/">Seat vs usage comparison</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/seat-vs-usage-pricing/">Guide: seat vs usage framework</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/usage-based-pricing/">Usage-based pricing</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/unit-economics/">Unit economics</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

